<%#
  Add Datafruit partial - converted from Ember AddDatafruit component (app/components/add-datafruit.hbs).
  The Ember component loaded microtexts (short user messages) via the API and displayed them
  in a marquee. It also allowed authenticated users to submit new microtexts.

  In Rails:
  - The microtext list is loaded via a Turbo Frame (with lazy loading from /api/microtexts)
  - Submission uses a Turbo Stream response to update the frame
  - The marquee display is kept for visual parity with the Ember app
%>
<%= turbo_frame_tag "add-datafruit", src: "/api/microtexts/current", loading: :lazy do %>
  <div class="text-sm sm:text-xl text-black px-2">
    <%# Placeholder while Turbo Frame loads %>
    <span>♪ ♪ ♪</span>
  </div>
<% end %>
